President Obama has announced his intent to nominate John Bryson as the Secretary of the U.S. Department of Commerce. Bryson brings decades of knowledge and experience in the public and private sectors and will play a key role in strengthening America's competitiveness around the world. The President is confident in Bryson's ability to promote job creation, economic growth, sustainable development, and improved standards of living for all Americans. Bryson will continue the Department's mission of driving U.S. competitiveness in the global marketplace, opening up new markets for U.S. goods and services, and supporting the President's goal of doubling America's exports. Bryson has a background in business and serves on the boards of several prominent companies and organizations. He is a graduate of Stanford University and Yale Law School.